The paper presents a combinatorial algorithm for solving symmetric diagonally dominant (SDD) linear systems, which involves constructing a spanning tree of a graph associated with the linear system and applying a simple update rule. This suggests that the paper could belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper presents a new algorithm for solving a specific type of linear system. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), as the paper deals with the numerical stability and implementation of the algorithm. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry), as the paper involves constructing a spanning tree of a graph. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), as the paper uses combinatorial techniques to solve the linear system. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper mentions the graph associated with the linear system, which could be interpreted as a network.
